    "summary": "I am a professional journalist, editor, translator, recipe developer and content creator. My focus is gastronomy, wine, travel, art, culture and lifestyle texts. I write in both Dutch and English (US & UK).\nIn 2007, I graduated from Leiden University in the department of Dutch Studies/Golden Age Art History.\nIn the summer of 1998, I attended the International Study Programme for Journalism at the Hogeschool voor de Journalistiek in Utrecht.\nCurrently, I am chief editor to the North American magazine DUTCH (USA/Canada) and the high-end glossy Discover Benelux (UK). I am also sub-editor to Inside Rotterdam (NL) and a regular contributor to Reader's Digest (UK). My work has appeared in top France publications FRANCE Magazine (UK), French Property News (UK), En Route (NL) and Leven in Frankrijk (NL). I had a regular food & drinks column in French Property News and En Route. I was also responsible for the food and drink news pages in FRANCE Magazine.\nMy recipes have appeared in the Dutch women's weekly Vriendin, and my articles have been published in leading magazines Bouillon (NL), Culture (USA) and b.spirit (UK).\nI am a professional translator for texts in my fields of expertise and have translated for Dutch publishing house Kosmos and newspaper Het Parool.\n\nList of publications I've worked with:\nReader's Digest\nFRANCE Magazine\nFrench Property News\nCULTURE the word on cheese\nDiscover Benelux\nDUTCH\nHet Parool\nBouillon\nEn Route\nLeven in Frankrijk\nInside Rotterdam\nb.spirit, (in-flight magazine Brussels Airlines)\nEastern Airways FR\nJamie Magazine Website\nHELLO Amsterdam\nDesserts Magazine\nFamily Matters Magazine\nYOU/RUSH Amsterdam\nAWAY Magazine, BE\nAckroyd Publications, BE\nThe Quercy & Gascony Local\nSchiphol Magazine\nThe Dutch Daily News\nThe Holland Times\nKoken.be\nHolland Focus\nXPat Journal\nZe.nl\nHonest Cooking\nThe Provence Sun\nThe Languedoc Sun\n\nBooks featuring my work:\n'Vis & Vega' (2011). Snor Publishers, Utrecht.\n'Borrelhapjeskalender' (2013). Snor Publishers, Utrecht.\n\nContact me for: Journalism on food, wine, travel, art and culture/Content creation, especially on food and drink/Recipe development/Food writing/Translations/Editing/Proofreading/Advertorials",
