                    "company": "La Douce Vie",
                    "description": "Contact me for:\n*Journalism:\nMy specialties are writing about food, wine, travel, lifestyle and culture. I have more than two decades of experience producing a wide variety of engaging content: from articles on travel, family and children, wine, lifestyle and history, to culinary columns, advertorials, book reviews and interviews. \n\n*Content creation, especially on France (travel, tourism, food & wine). Let me promote your region or business. I can offer you a full package deal that includes text, enticing photography, beautifully designed brochures (digital/print) and even professional film. Our mission is to make your destination or product shine, and our prices are competitive. Our services are available in English (UK & US) and Dutch. \n\n*Writing and editing of all kinds of texts:\nChoosing the right words; paying meticulous attention to proper spelling, grammar, punctuation and syntax; adhering to your publication\u2019s style and tone. I am the editor and senior vice president of the North American publication DUTCH, sub-editor and journalist for Inside Rotterdam. I was a regular writer, editor and translator for the Amsterdam-based tourist publication HELLO Amsterdam. I have also edited and translated tourist magazines such as RUSH and YOU.\n\n*Recipe development: \nI have written recipes for a wide variety of publications, including one of the most popular Dutch women\u2019s weekly magazines, Vriendin. My recipes are tested for taste and accuracy, and are always guaranteed to work, even for novice cooks.\n\n*Translations: \nI have a degree in academic Dutch from the University of Leiden and have lived in the Netherlands for more than two decades. I have translated menus, newspaper articles, press releases, books and more. \n\n*Culinary consultancy\n\n*Cooking films:\nI can produce content in English or Dutch, and my work is accompanied by high-resolution professional photography at no extra cost. Video can also be delivered upon request.\n\nMORE INFORMATION: www.thefrenchlife.org",
